HEADWORD: Sensualize
<hw>Sen"su*al*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Sensualized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Sensualizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To
make sensual; to subject to the love of sensual pleasure; to debase by
carnal gratifications; to carnalize; <as>as, <ex>sensualized</ex> by
pleasure</as>.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By the neglect of prayer, the thoughts are
<qex>sensualized</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>T. H. Skinner.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sensually</ent>⟦br⟧
